---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import StructuredData from '../components/StructuredData.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About Chris Smith | Start & Scale Growth Advisory"
	description="15+ years scaling revenue inside WeWork, CloudKitchens, and Apple. Growth advisory grounded in operating experience, not frameworks."
	canonical="/about"
>
	<StructuredData type="organization" />

	<!-- Hero -->
			<section class="bg-dark pt-32 pb-16 sm:pt-40 sm:pb-20 lg:pt-48 lg:pb-28">
				<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8">
					<h1 class="font-display text-white text-h1 lg:text-[3.75rem] lg:leading-[1.05] max-w-4xl">
						I've built revenue orgs inside companies most people only read about.
					</h1>
					<p class="text-body-lg text-body-light mt-6 max-w-2xl">
						15 years inside founder-led companies. WeWork under Adam, CloudKitchens under Travis, Apple under Steve. I launched markets, closed enterprise deals, built teams, and kept execution moving across orgs that didn't report to me.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Career Arc -->
			<section class="bg-background py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
				<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8">
					<h2 class="font-display text-headline text-h2 lg:text-[3rem] lg:leading-[1.1]">Where I've been</h2>
					<p class="text-body-lg text-body mt-4 max-w-2xl">Five companies. All founder-led. All moving faster than their systems could handle.</p>

					<div class="mt-10 space-y-8 lg:space-y-10">
						<!-- TESF -->
						<div class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 sm:pl-8">
							<p class="text-small text-body uppercase tracking-wider">2009 – Present</p>
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h3 mt-2">TESF — Chief Advancement Officer</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-3 max-w-3xl">
								Co-founded a national 501(c)(3) that now operates across 29 states. Lead operations, fundraising, and technology modernization. This is where the systems-building started.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- Apple -->
						<div class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 sm:pl-8">
							<p class="text-small text-body uppercase tracking-wider">2010 – 2013</p>
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h3 mt-2">Apple Retail — Team Lead, Business Sales</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-3 max-w-3xl">
								Led 15 Business Specialists in Apple's highest-grossing store. 175 SMB and enterprise clients. $7M+ in revenue across 12 quarters. Top 1% globally three consecutive years: 140%, 164%, 131% of plan.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- WeWork -->
						<div class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 sm:pl-8">
							<p class="text-small text-body uppercase tracking-wider">2014 – 2020</p>
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h3 mt-2">WeWork — Community Manager → Regional Sales Director</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-3 max-w-3xl">
								Early employee. Promoted four times in five and a half years. Scaled regional ARR from $20M to $120M in 24 months across 21 locations. Led 7 market launches. Closed $70M+ in enterprise deals with Amazon, Puma, EzCater, and the U.S. Air Force. Top performer globally four consecutive years. Stayed through the IPO run, the restructuring, and the layoffs.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- CloudKitchens -->
						<div class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 sm:pl-8">
							<p class="text-small text-body uppercase tracking-wider">2020 – 2021</p>
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h3 mt-2">CloudKitchens — Northeast Business Lead</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-3 max-w-3xl">
								Deployed by the COO to build the Northeast from scratch. Recruited a 42-person org (AEs, SDRs, CSMs) and launched 9 markets in 8 months. Hit 120%+ of plan. 40% faster time-to-revenue than any other region.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- Allwhere -->
						<div class="border-l-2 border-accent pl-6 sm:pl-8">
							<p class="text-small text-body uppercase tracking-wider">2022</p>
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h3 mt-2">Allwhere — Head of Sales & Partnerships</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-3 max-w-3xl">
								Stealth-stage startup. Built the GTM strategy from zero. Generated 50% of total company revenue in 6 months. 210% of plan. 35% of new logos.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Why Work With Me -->
			<section class="bg-surface py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
				<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8">
					<h2 class="font-display text-headline text-h2 lg:text-[3rem] lg:leading-[1.1]">Why work with me</h2>

					<div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 lg:gap-8 mt-10">
						<!-- Differentiator 1 -->
						<div class="bg-background p-6 lg:p-8 rounded">
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h4">I've operated inside hypergrowth, not studied it.</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-4">
								Most consultants know hypergrowth from case studies. I know it from the org chart that changed monthly, the systems that broke under load, and the timelines that got cut in half on a Thursday. WeWork, CloudKitchens, and Apple taught me what scaling feels like at the operational level.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- Differentiator 2 -->
						<div class="bg-background p-6 lg:p-8 rounded">
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h4">I lead across functions without direct authority.</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-4">
								Same pattern at every company: walk into a cross-functional problem across sales, marketing, ops, and CS. Impose clarity. Drive accountability. Keep execution moving, usually with teams that don't report to me. Founders need this constantly and struggle to hire for it.
							</p>
						</div>

						<!-- Differentiator 3 -->
						<div class="bg-background p-6 lg:p-8 rounded">
							<h3 class="font-display text-headline text-h4">I build the technology myself.</h3>
							<p class="text-body text-body mt-4">
								I built a full-stack SaaS platform end-to-end: React, TypeScript, Supabase, 19 Edge Functions, AI document processing. I configure Salesforce, deploy marketing automation, and ship production code. When I recommend a system, I can implement it. No handoff to another vendor. No six-month integration project.
							</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- CTA Block -->
			<section class="bg-dark py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
				<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-5 sm:px-8 text-center">
					<h2 class="font-display text-white text-h2 lg:text-[3rem] lg:leading-[1.1]">Curious whether we'd be a fit?</h2>
					<p class="text-body-lg text-body-light mt-4 max-w-xl mx-auto">30 minutes. No pitch, no deck. Just a conversation about where you are and what might move the needle.</p>
					<div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4 items-center">
						<a href="/contact" class="bg-accent text-white text-btn px-7 py-3.5 rounded hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors duration-150 cursor-pointer inline-block">
							Book a Call
						</a>
						<a href="/contact" class="text-body-light text-btn hover:text-white transition-colors duration-150 cursor-pointer inline-block py-3.5">
							Or send a message &rarr;
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
</BaseLayout>
